==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obliquation
<hw>Ob`li*qua"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>obliquatio</ets>, fr. <ets>obliquare</ets> to turn obliquely. See
<er>Oblique</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of becoming oblique; a
turning to one side; obliquity; <as>as, the <ex>obligation</ex> of the
eyes</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Deviation from moral rectitude.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oblique</ent>⟦br⟧
